# Pre-Execution Setup

Before starting a session, create or verify:

```text
qa-artifacts/
├── screenshots/
├── network-logs/
├── console-logs/
├── traces/
├── downloads/
├── db-validation/
├── bugs/
└── session-report.md
```

Capture session metadata:

- feature
- environment URL
- browser
- viewport
- operating system, if known
- test source
- suite or run ID
- build/version, if available
- tester
- start time
- repository branch/commit, if available

## Environment Readiness Checklist

Verify:

- target URL is reachable
- login works for required role
- test user or role exists
- required seed data exists
- feature flag is enabled
- dependencies are available
- browser storage is clean before first test
- viewport matches scope
- network and console capture are enabled where possible
- Qase test run is available if results must be reported there

If the environment fails readiness checks, stop or mark affected cases as blocked.

