# Qase Result Notes

When updating Qase, use clear notes.

## PASS Note

```text
Passed. Verified expected UI state, navigation, and relevant network behavior.
```

## FAIL Note

```text
Failed at Step [N]. Expected [expected]. Actual [actual]. Evidence: [artifact path]. Bug candidate: [BUG-ID or pending].
```

## BLOCKED Note

```text
Blocked. Unable to execute because [reason]. Required action: [what must be fixed or provided].
```

## SKIPPED Note

```text
Skipped because [reason]. This case was outside the confirmed execution scope.
```

Do not put raw enum numbers in user-facing notes.

---

# Bug Handoff

For each failure that appears to be a product defect, prepare a bug handoff for the bug-reporting rule.

Include:

- summary
- environment
- preconditions
- steps to reproduce
- expected result
- actual result
- test data
- severity recommendation
- priority recommendation
- evidence files
- console logs
- network logs
- suspected component
- affected test case ID
- affected requirement ID

If a failure is caused by a bad test case, recommend updating the test case instead of filing a product bug.

---

# Execution Quality Rules

- Never mark PASS without verifying every expected result.
- Never mark FAIL without evidence.
- Never rely only on visual impression when API or DB behavior is part of the expected result.
- Never use fixed sleeps as the primary wait strategy.
- Never continue blindly after repeated environment failures.
- Never store sensitive tokens, passwords, or real PII in artifacts.
- Never use production data unless explicitly approved.
- Never modify destructive or irreversible data outside a safe test environment.
- Always reset state when the case requires independence.
- Always use exact UI labels when interacting with elements.
- Always capture screenshots and logs for failures.
- Always mark Qase results immediately when Qase is available.
- Always distinguish product defect, test defect, environment issue, and requirement ambiguity.
- Always record blocked/skipped reasons.
- Always maintain the session report.

